name: Supermoon
summary: On October 9-10, skywatchers will witness the "Hunter's Supermoon," the largest full moon of 2024. This celestial event is known as a supermoon because it occurs when a full moon coincides with the moon's closest approach to Earth, resulting in an unusually large and bright moon in the sky. The Hunter's Moon is named after a traditional time for hunting in the fall. Observers can expect to see this supermoon rising in the eastern sky just after sunset on October 9th, with optimal viewing conditions expected late that night and into the early morning hours of October 10th. The supermoon's increased brightness and size make it an ideal time for celestial photography and stargazing enthusiasts to capture stunning images of this unique lunar event.

Despite hitting a leadoff homer in Game 4 of the NLCS, Ohtani's overall batting average for the playoffs remains low. The legal battle over who will receive the proceeds from the sale adds another layer of drama to Ohtani's already challenging postseason experience.

name: Robert Roberson
summary: Robert Roberson, facing execution for a shaken baby syndrome case, has received a stay of execution from the Texas Supreme Court. Despite a failed clemency plea and an attempt to vacate his execution warrant, Roberson's execution remains on hold while he awaits a decision from Governor Abbott. The case has sparked bipartisan support for his defense, with arguments that he may have been wrongly convicted due to outdated scientific knowledge about shaken baby syndrome. The Texas Board of Pardons and Paroles rejected Roberson's clemency plea, but the Innocence Project, a non-profit that fights wrongful convictions, continues to advocate for his innocence. The case has drawn national attention, with Supreme Court Justice Sotomayor dissenting in the decision to deny Roberson's appeal and legal expert John Grisham expressing concerns about the fairness of Roberson's trial. A GOP megadonor is also leading efforts to convince Governor Abbott to grant clemency, adding political pressure to the situation.

The Saints have declared the game against the Broncos as "Black Thursday" in honor of Brees.

summary: Harvard University is facing a decline in donations, with a drop of over $150 million in its endowment. Researchers have also discovered a papyrus containing lost scenes from Euripides' plays. Additionally, big donors are offering suggestions on how to improve the university. In other news, Harvard Elementary is receiving support from district officials for its IB certification, while Hastings men are accused of attempted murder in a Harvard hit. President Garber has expressed disappointment with fundraising numbers, but the endowment has still grown to $53.2 billion with a 9.6% return in 2024.
